result.name: CHA DON

reviews.text:
May be just my experience was bad and chose the wrong food, but I don't think I will be returning.
Anyway, I had this red bean in egg white toast, the red beans are in between 2 thick white bread....so taste quite separate and plain
The lady wasn't shouting rude, but not exactly polite.  Just don't want to work attitude
Nice local style decoration is the highlight. However, its overpriced as food quality was not satisfying.
Very special decorations with themes of old Hong Kong. Good food is just a bonus. The downside is that there are a lot of dishes in the menu were actually not available, very disappointing.
Kowloon City culture decorations. Good food. Enjoyable.
Food was unexpectedly food! simple but interesting combinations!

result.name: 港嘢茶檔

reviews.text:
港嘢 : 麥香包 + 流沙包 + 紫薯包 (蒸)，意想不到的好吃 ! 
再次過來吃午飯 ，叉燒炒蛋飯 ，大大碟 ;  沙嗲牛肉出前一丁湯麵套餐 ，湯底太鹹 ，麵包鬆軟可口 👍
茶檔的奶茶應該很有水準, 但呢間無論是凍或熱的都非常唔掂

這是我第一次來港嘢, 環境不錯, 很有懷舊感.

可能是下午3點多的關係, 人客不多, 兩個人, 坐在靠牆的小圓枱, 算是舒適(其實是放了4張凳).

食物味道都不錯, 價錢也不貴, 點了個C常餐, 56元, 有: 蕃茄濃湯午餐肉粒通粉+炒蛋+茄汁焗豆+多士+熱飲, 抵食, 維一要提的是蕃茄湯太酸, 連我這個平時很能食酸的人也受不了, 有待改善。
懷舊裝修，食物有水準，但款式比較少，一個字，好
好食， 但稍嫌貴左少少;可能想保持食物質素啦，外賣用得比較多膠。。。
